IF: Instruction Fetch
- save instruction from pc in if/id
- increment pc address and write back for next cycle
- save pc in if/id(prep for beq)

ID:Instruction Decode(and rf read)
- store sign expanded imm, rs1 and rs2 in id/ex;
- store pc address in id/ex

IF, ID executed for all instructions

EX: Execute
- stores results of execution

MEM: Memory(access data memory)
- read data memory using address from ex/mem
- load data into mem/wb

WB: Write back
- read data from mem/wb and write it to register file

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- each datapath component can only be used within ONE pipeline stage, or else there would be a structural hazard. 
- each control signal only needs ot be set at a particular pipeline stage(cause its associated with omponents that are active only in a single stage)

- we send all control signals at ID and they get carried forward to different stages...(?)

  |pipeline stage | signal |
  --------------------------
    IF   none
    ID   none
    EX   ALUop, ALUsrc
    MEM  MemRead, MemWrite, Branch, PCsrc (selects the next sequential address unless Branch == 0 && ALUout == 0)
    WB   MemtoReg, RegWrite

